# AI Provider Integration Guide

**Last Updated:** November 19, 2025
**Status:** ✅ Active
**Source:** Validated from codebase audit + Gemini analysis

---

## Overview

This guide outlines the standard procedure for integrating new AI providers into the Neuman Brain ecosystem. Our architecture uses a unified `AIProvider` interface to ensure consistency, security, and error handling across all AI services.

## Current Architecture

**Location:** `src/services/ai/`

**Core Files:**
- **`types.ts`** - Defines the `AIProvider` interface and shared types
- **`providerRouter.ts`** - Handles fallback logic and provider selection
- **`[providerName]Provider.ts`** - Individual provider implementations

**Supported Providers (8 total):**
1. OpenRouter - 200+ models, free tier (primary)
2. Groq - Fast inference
3. HuggingFace - Open-source models
4. Mistral - European AI, GDPR compliant
5. Gemini - Google AI, 1M token context
6. OpenAI - GPT-4o, o1 models
7. Anthropic - Claude 3.5 Sonnet
8. xAI - Grok models

---

## Adding a New Provider

### Step 1: Define the Provider

Create a new file: `src/services/ai/[providerName]Provider.ts`

**Template:**
```typescript
import { AIProvider, AIModel, AIMessageOptions, AIResponse } from './types';
import { ProviderError, ProviderErrorType } from './types';

// Define available models
const MODELS: AIModel[] = [
  {
    id: 'model-id',
    name: 'Model Display Name',
    provider: 'my-provider',
    speedRating: 4, // 1-5 (1=slow, 5=lightning fast)
    qualityRating: 4, // 1-5 (1=basic, 5=excellent)
    contextWindow: 128000, // Max tokens
    maxOutputTokens: 4096,
    supportsStreaming: true,
    supportsVision: false,
    supportsFunctionCalling: true,
    isFree: true, // Available on free tier?
    costPer1MTokens: 0.01, // Cost if paid
    requiresApiKey: true,
    useCases: ['chat', 'code', 'reasoning'], // Use case tags
    description: 'Brief description of model strengths',
  },
];

// Provider implementation
export const myNewProvider: AIProvider = {
  metadata: {
    id: 'my-provider',
    name: 'My Provider',
    displayName: 'My Provider AI',
    description: 'Description of the provider',
    requiresApiKey: true,
    apiKeyUrl: 'https://provider.com/api-keys',
    apiKeyLabel: 'My Provider API Key',
    hasFreeModels: true,
    freeModelIds: ['free-model-id'],
    freeTierLimits: {
      requestsPerMinute: 10,
      requestsPerDay: 100,
      tokensPerMinute: 10000,
      description: '10 req/min, 100 req/day (free tier)',
    },
    supportsCORS: true, // Can be called from browser?
    requiresProxy: false,
    supportsStreaming: true,
    websiteUrl: 'https://provider.com',
    docsUrl: 'https://provider.com/docs',
  },

  models: MODELS,

  // API key stored in IndexedDB (AES-256-GCM encrypted)
  isConfigured(): boolean {
    const { useTerminalStore } = require('../../stores/useTerminalStore');
    const providers = useTerminalStore.getState().providers;
    return providers['my-provider']?.apiKey !== undefined;
  },

  setApiKey(apiKey: string): void {
    const { useTerminalStore } = require('../../stores/useTerminalStore');
    useTerminalStore.getState().setProviderApiKey('my-provider', apiKey);
  },

  getApiKey(): string | null {
    const { useTerminalStore } = require('../../stores/useTerminalStore');
    const providers = useTerminalStore.getState().providers;
    return providers['my-provider']?.apiKey || null;
  },

  clearApiKey(): void {
    const { useTerminalStore } = require('../../stores/useTerminalStore');
    useTerminalStore.getState().clearProviderApiKey('my-provider');
  },

  async validateApiKey(apiKey: string): Promise<boolean> {
    try {
      // Make a test API call to validate the key
      const response = await fetch('https://api.provider.com/v1/models', {
        headers: {
          'Authorization': `Bearer ${apiKey}`,
        },
      });
      return response.ok;
    } catch {
      return false;
    }
  },

  getModel(modelId: string): AIModel | null {
    return MODELS.find((m) => m.id === modelId) || null;
  },

  getDefaultModel(): AIModel {
    return MODELS[0]; // Return first free model
  },

  getFreeModels(): AIModel[] {
    return MODELS.filter((m) => m.isFree);
  },

  async sendMessage(modelId: string, options: AIMessageOptions): Promise<AIResponse> {
    const apiKey = this.getApiKey();
    if (!apiKey) {
      throw new ProviderError(
        ProviderErrorType.INVALID_API_KEY,
        'API key required',
        'my-provider',
        false
      );
    }

    try {
      const response = await fetch('https://api.provider.com/v1/chat/completions', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          'Authorization': `Bearer ${apiKey}`,
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          model: modelId,
          messages: [
            ...(options.systemPrompt ? [{ role: 'system', content: options.systemPrompt }] : []),
            ...(options.conversationHistory || []),
            { role: 'user', content: options.prompt },
          ],
          temperature: options.temperature || 0.7,
          max_tokens: options.maxTokens || 2048,
          stream: options.stream || false,
        }),
      });

      if (!response.ok) {
        const error = await response.json();

        // Map provider errors to standard error types
        if (response.status === 401) {
          throw new ProviderError(
            ProviderErrorType.INVALID_API_KEY,
            'Invalid API key',
            'my-provider',
            false
          );
        } else if (response.status === 429) {
          throw new ProviderError(
            ProviderErrorType.RATE_LIMIT,
            'Rate limit exceeded',
            'my-provider',
            true // Retryable
          );
        } else {
          throw new ProviderError(
            ProviderErrorType.UNKNOWN,
            error.message || 'Provider error',
            'my-provider',
            false
          );
        }
      }

      const data = await response.json();

      return {
        content: data.choices[0].message.content,
        model: modelId,
        provider: 'my-provider',
        finishReason: 'stop',
        usage: {
          promptTokens: data.usage?.prompt_tokens || 0,
          completionTokens: data.usage?.completion_tokens || 0,
          totalTokens: data.usage?.total_tokens || 0,
        },
      };
    } catch (error) {
      if (error instanceof ProviderError) {
        throw error;
      }
      throw new ProviderError(
        ProviderErrorType.NETWORK_ERROR,
        error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Network error',
        'my-provider',
        true // Network errors are retryable
      );
    }
  },
};
```

### Step 2: Register the Provider

Update `src/services/ai/providerRouter.ts`:

```typescript
import { myNewProvider } from './myNewProvider';

const PROVIDERS: Record<string, AIProvider> = {
  openrouter: openRouterProvider,
  groq: groqProvider,
  huggingface: huggingFaceProvider,
  mistral: mistralProvider,
  gemini: geminiProvider,
  openai: openaiProvider,
  anthropic: anthropicProvider,
  xai: xaiProvider,
  'my-provider': myNewProvider, // Add here
};
```

### Step 3: Update UI (Automatic)

The UI automatically renders all registered providers:
- `src/components/ProviderSettings.tsx` - Shows provider in settings
- `src/components/ModelSelector.tsx` - Shows models in selector

**No manual UI updates needed!**

---

## Security Requirements

### API Key Storage

**NEVER hardcode API keys.** All keys are:
1. Encrypted using **AES-256-GCM** (WebCrypto API)
2. Stored in **IndexedDB** (not localStorage)
3. Password-protected with **PBKDF2** (100,000 iterations, SHA-256)
4. Keys expire after 30 days (user must re-enter password)

**Implementation:**
```typescript
// Keys stored in useTerminalStore via encrypted IndexedDB
const { useTerminalStore } = require('../../stores/useTerminalStore');
useTerminalStore.getState().setProviderApiKey('provider-id', apiKey);
```

### CORS & Privacy

**Preferred:** Direct browser-to-API calls (Zero-Data-Host architecture)
- No server proxy
- User's API key stays on their device
- Privacy-first approach

**If CORS is an issue:**
- User can configure their own proxy
- **NEVER** use a central proxy (violates privacy model)

---

## Error Handling

### Standard Error Types

All providers must use `ProviderError` class:

```typescript
import { ProviderError, ProviderErrorType } from './types';

// Error types:
ProviderErrorType.INVALID_API_KEY  // 401 - API key invalid
ProviderErrorType.RATE_LIMIT       // 429 - Rate limit exceeded (retryable)
ProviderErrorType.QUOTA_EXCEEDED   // 429 - Quota exceeded (retryable)
ProviderErrorType.MODEL_NOT_FOUND  // 404 - Model doesn't exist
ProviderErrorType.NETWORK_ERROR    // Network/timeout (retryable)
ProviderErrorType.TIMEOUT          // Request timeout (retryable)
ProviderErrorType.UNKNOWN          // Other errors
```

### Auto-Fallback System

The `AIProviderRouter` automatically falls back to alternative providers when:
- Rate limit exceeded
- Quota exceeded
- Network errors
- Timeouts

**Fallback order (default):**
1. OpenRouter (best flexibility)
2. Groq (best speed)
3. HuggingFace (free fallback)
4. Mistral (European option)
5. Gemini (Google fallback)

**User is notified** when fallback occurs (configurable).

---

## Testing Checklist

Before submitting a new provider integration:

**Functionality:**
- [ ] API key validation works
- [ ] sendMessage returns correct response format
- [ ] Error handling maps provider errors correctly
- [ ] Free models identified correctly
- [ ] Streaming works (if supported)

**Security:**
- [ ] No hardcoded API keys
- [ ] Uses encrypted storage (useTerminalStore)
- [ ] Validates API key before requests
- [ ] Proper error messages (no sensitive data leaked)

**UX:**
- [ ] Provider appears in Settings > AI Terminal
- [ ] Models appear in Model Selector
- [ ] Free models marked correctly
- [ ] Rate limits documented in metadata

**Performance:**
- [ ] No unnecessary API calls
- [ ] Proper timeout handling
- [ ] Streaming works smoothly (if supported)

---

## Related Documentation

- **Type Definitions:** `src/services/ai/types.ts`
- **Provider Router:** `src/services/ai/providerRouter.ts`
- **AI Terminal UI:** `src/components/AITerminal.tsx`
- **Encrypted Storage:** `src/stores/useTerminalStore.ts`
- **Multi-Provider Terminal:** `docs/technical/multi_provider_ai_terminal.md` (if exists)

